title: Avengers: Doomsday (2026) - First Trailer | Marvel
comment:
Oh this is easy, my list isn’t ranked about how much I want them tho

1. UCS AT-AT: beautiful set and the AT-AT is my favorite troop carrier tied with the ATTE
2. 2007 MTT: honestly I don’t need to say much but it is a perfect set. This MTT is timeless
3. AT-OT with drop ship: if you can’t tell already I’m a big army builder and I would love to have this amazing set which Lego should buy probably will never remake
4. Death Star Play Set: just such a fun set and some say it’s ugly but I think it looks rly cool and I would love to have it in my collection
5. UCS Star Destroyer: the ISD is easily my favorite Star Wars vehicle because of how just damn menacing it is. Death Star is a close second but just seeing an ISD come into the atmosphere right when the rebels just won an exhausting brutal fight will never not be the most bad ass thing I can think of.

I have a few honorable mentions ofc
1. UCS Venator: just so badass man
2. Palpatines arrest: cmon, who doesn’t like this set?
3. The Malevolence: so badass, easily best CIS imo

comment: In Avengers: Doomsday, RDJ returns as a Tony Stark variant who became Doctor Doom after losing his world. Believing the only way to save the multiverse is total control, he uses Stark tech, mutant DNA & Kang remnants to build a device that merges all timelines. The Avengers, X-Men, Fantastic Four & Loki team up to stop him as incursions spiral out of control. Doom nearly wins—until a memory of his daughter breaks him. The machine is destroyed, the multiverse barely survives… but the heroes are scattered across alternate realities.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
I don't think people really realize what Doomsday and Secret Wars really represent. These two films are not simply blockbusters packed with action and special effects. No... they are much more than that. It not only signals the end of the MCU but also of all the other Marvel superhero universes that have existed for years. Whether it's Fox's X-Men, the Sonyverse with Venom or Morbius, the animated universe of Miles Morales, all the series from the 2000s like Avengers Assemble or even the comics. Everything we know about this universe will never be the same after these two projects. Projects that will make us think about everything we went through to get there and that will make us say to ourselves that this world has changed a lot since our childhood. A time that seemed so long ago, but when we watched Spider-Man's adventures on TV, when we started debating who was better between Captain America and Iron Man, when the first MCU films came out and everyone was talking about them. Life may not have been so simple for each of us, but at least these universes could allow us to escape for a moment and forget the harsh reality of the world.

And despite the fact that I'm only 16 years old and I admit that I wasn't a big fan of Marvel as a child. I must admit that I feel proud to be part of this generation that will have the opportunity to attend an event like this. I remember totally missing out on Infinity War and Endgame when they came out. So if I'm also looking forward to seeing Doomsday and Secret Wars, it's because I see seeing them as a way to make up for that time when I missed this huge hype in 2018-19. And yes indeed, these two films are going to be full of cameos, that's for sure. But I don't see any harm in it personally, as long as it's done in a good way anyway. In short, I'm really happy with this casting and even though I'm sure we've only seen about 30-40% of the actors who will be in Doomsday, I still have great confidence in the Russo brothers to make these two Avengers movies the best in the entire MCU .

and even if after 2027 will come a whole new era of superheroes maybe less good than this one, let me tell you that I would always be happy to immerse myself in this incredible world where imagination has no limits and where the possibilities are infinite.

Long live the MCU, the Avengers, the Guardians, the Fantastic Four, the Thunderbolts, the X-Men, the TVA, all the heroes and other characters who have continued to fuel this incredible universe but above all... Long live Stan Lee !

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment: Having RDJ come back as Victor Von Doom reeks of desperation. Where it’s nice to see them bring back nostalgic X-men, throwing a bunch of names and heroes into one move isn’t the answer. It only worked in Infinity Wars and Endgame cause there was 10-15 years of build up and interconnecting stories that came to a climax. It was brilliant storytelling and filmmaking. Now, it’s just a trend. And to have RDJ back in the MCU is %100 the wrong move. His face is always going to be connected to Iron Man. Whether you want to admit it or not. It’s already bad……but If they try to write in some absurd multiverse story where Iron Man is Von Doom……C’mon are you serious? I really hope not. But wouldn’t be surprised. Either way. This is off to a horrible start. Axing RDJ is the only way to at least TRY and save this movie…..let alone the MCU.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
There’s no build up to this movie. The Infinity Saga had a build up to the first Avengers movie then Ultron then infinity War but Phase 2 feels completely disjointed and unfocused. We need a Shang Chi 2 before Doomsday. It just feels all over the place. Too many heroes yet also not enough because where’s Dr. Strange? Vision? Hawk Eye? What’s happening with Blade? Why are you guys using Sir Ian McKellen? Don’t get me wrong I love him but he’s old as now, what about Fassbender and McAvoy? I’m legit so confused. Do I have to watch all your announcements to keep up with what’s going on?

With all these names it feels like the budget of the movie could blow out completely and they’ll struggle to make a profit on it. Phase 1 of the Infinity Saga was great partly because it was *simple*. Four heroes, five movies and then the ensemble movie. Now it’s like wtf is going on?

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Couple things. Mostly pessimistic because I’ve seen, (I believe), the highs of this franchise.

1) Remember when it wasn’t the trailers that got people hyped? The (mostly) high quality stories led into the next film. It wasn’t the anticipation of the next showing, but the confidence in the prior that made you interested in the further stories.

Thanos was introduced more than a decade before his actual introduction and is without doubt the best villain slightly due to that fact.

Obviously it’s impossible to recreate that, but the stories between his post-credit introduction and the death of Loki are what made his threat so impactful.

Most of the movies made the characters grow to where they were in Infinity War - that’s not nearly as true with the new cast. All due respect to the actors, but they’re not going to be seen the same as Chris Evans, RDJ (as Iron man), Hiddleston, Ruffalo, Johansson, or many others. Not because they are lessor in their respective parts but because they don’t have the time to grow as characters like those we witnessed prior to the huge collective narrative.

2) No Spider-Man (yet). Womp womp.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
I have a theory: the chairs go beyond simply revealing the cast names.

1) Could this be a deliberate foreshadowing of Doom's influence, with the displayed names signaling those he will defeat, manipulate, or reshape to fit his vision?

If this is just the first wave of reveals, the next set of names could represent those who survive, rebel, or challenge Doom later on.

Are these characters doomed? (Yes, probably lol)

For example, Doom could:
- Erase or rewrite their existence, leading to a complete restructuring of the Marvel Universe under his control
- Replace them with alternate versions of themselves
- Force them to serve or oppose him in a battle for control over reality

2) They could be just the characters that exist in Doctor Doom's universe

3) The absence of key characters, like Doctor Strange, suggests that this casting reveal is far from a random setup...or it could be a completely random reveal...who knows, lol

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment: The Infinity War saga had a clear structure: a beginning with individual character movies, a middle where heroes were assembled, and an ending that culminated in their joint confrontation against a formidable threat in Endgame. In contrast, the phase following Endgame seems to only offer a prologue, focusing on the emergence of new heroes rooted in the legacy of their predecessors, but faltering due to poor writing that prevents them from progressing to a meaningful middle. Consequently, Marvel's solution has been to reboot with new characters. The pressing question now is whether Marvel has learned from the past five years, or if this upcoming film is destined to falter before it even has the chance to launch a new phase.

comment: Aside from the disappointing project marvel has churned out over the last few years, I think the biggest problem I’ve had with marvel is the poor planning. So many green lights and then cancellations (blade being a big example of that). Marvel needs a hit and they know this IP will likely do well. I have lately thought that I haven’t been excited but this teaser drop gave me a lot of goosebumps. They’re bringing back Alan Silversti and I love his scores of the first films. The teasing of the  X-men theme combined with the avengers theme is absolute genius and perhaps the X-men characters associated with this project is perhaps the main reason why I’ve got a hype for a marvel film I haven’t felt in a long time. I really look forward to seeing the progress of this film.

comment:
The return of the original X-Men is the only real pull for me and I’m still going to wait for reviewers I trust to see it first. If they say it’s good, I might go see it in theaters if they say it’s decent to okay, I’ll stream it. If it’s fair or worse, I’ll probably never watch it. Marvel has burned too much of faith in their ability to tell a decent story.
And I used to be a massive fan. I saw every movie, opening weekend if not opening day from Iron Man to Black Widow. With the exception of Spiderman: No Way Home, Marvel hasn’t made a movie since Endgame that I would consider on par with a pre-Endgame film. (and technically Sony made Spider-Man.🤷‍♂️)

comment: It just occurs to me that despite this huge cast, most of these characters aren’t Avengers. Not counting RDJ as he is playing Doom Chris Hemsworth’s Thor is the only one of the original main six on here. You got Anthony Mackie’s Captain America, he was an Avenger in his Falcon days and Paul Rudd’s Ant-Man. That’s kind of it. I don’t know if Bucky was an official Avenger despite being part of Team Cap and fighting alongside them in the Battles of Wakanda and Earth? But he will be a Thunderbolt. title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
This shows enormous promise. If anyone can pull off being both Stark and Doom, it's Downey. The writing challenges here will be considerable, but if they nail it, they could get back on their game.

Interesting that there is no Hulk or Captain Marvel. I'd prefer both to Sentry, who is kind of a schlocky character, IMO. No Spidey, no Ms. Marvel, no new Hawkeye, no Moon Knight, no Vision.

But also...Doom is largely mystical. Seems odd to have no mystic heroes there. Gosh, it's a darn shame that they lit the credibility and/or the sympathetic nature of both of their great mystical heroes on fire so Sam Raimi could make a gag film (Multiverse of Madness) without having even watched the previous material (as stated by Elizabeth Olson said).

I know they can't have everyone, but leaving magic/mysticism totally out on the heroes side feels like a bad idea.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment: Awesome. Another Marvel movie. Finally. So this time Tony Starks evil twin brother wants to take over the universe. I imagine it could play out like Empire strikes back, Evil Victor reveals himself to Good Tony and says "Im am your brother, Tony!". What a cinematic moment that would be. Possible spoiler alert: Most likely Tony will have a goatee while Victor will have not, so that we can clearly differentiate between them. After Captain America, the cinematic bar has been set high and the demand is huge, so this better be better than just epic. Hopefully they will add singing and dancing scenes, a bit like Joker, and we could have flashbacks of a very young Tony and Victor going to school together - things that will push the Multiverse into another dimension, where it rightfully belongs to. Speaking of which, maybe, hopefully, the Doomsday ending will be left wide open, a dark glooming cliffhanger but with a twist many have been waiting for - or rather dreamt about. When im attending the marvel and disney cons, we always agree on what the Multiverse needs next. We, well - me, and the people I usually chat up at the cons - at the end of Doomsday, Dr. Strange shows up or Thanos, or Flash or maybe the blue guy from that Watchmen movie. Whoever it is, it needs to be someone who is able to open up some Multiverse portal and/or travel through time too (optional). So at the end, when Victor Doom takes over the univere, laughing maliciously, our hero opens up the portal and the Power Rangers come jumping through it, ready to face their worst enemy yet. They kick and punch Victor through the portal, where he dissapears. The portal closes and the Rangers are now stuck with the Avengers in their world. All that leads us into the next movie : "Avenger x Rangers : Double Trouble". Lets dream a little dream.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
My biggest concern for this movie is how they will handle Loki and his “timeline situation”. The ending of Loki season 2 made me very worried despite Loki’s noble sacrifice, because you can’t sit an imperfect person on a throne that demands perfection for all of time and expect everything to go well.
Maybe someone or something else will come along. Maybe, since the timelines were once independent and self-sustained (before he who remains came along), they will re-learn how to be such. My point is that, if Loki is going to be in this movie, I hope that means his situation will be different in some meaningful way by the end.
Also Thor and Loki are in the same movie for the first time in years… so… fingers crossed.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
This is a Doctor Doom multiverse version of Tony Stark. In this universe, Tony wasn't sacrificed in Endgame. That’s why Doctor Strange never told him what would happen—because if Tony knew he was going to die, he wouldn’t have made the sacrifice. Instead, he survives, learns about the multiverse, and, being Tony, he takes it upon himself to protect it.

With the Infinity Stones, he’s practically unstoppable, but what he doesn’t realize is that he is the real threat to the multiverse. His fear of failure, his obsession with control—those are what turn him into Doctor Doom.

RDJ is going to kill this role. We’ve seen him play more than just Iron Man, and we know he has the range to bring this darker, more complex version of Tony to life!

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment: My God, I've never been so excited to hear the X-Men theme blended with the Avengers theme in such a way that gives me MAJOR goosebumps!!! This enormous, stacked cast, this surprise announcement, and every single name announced one chair at a time, I'm so ready and I'm so not ready at the same time!! I literally cheered when I saw Simu Liu (Shang-Chi) and Tom Hiddleston's (Loki) names on those chairs! You know whose names I wasn't expecting to show in this movie? The six original X-Men from the Fox Universe: Professor X, Beast, Nightcrawler, Mystique, Cyclops, and least of all, MAGNETO!! I have a strong feeling this is only just the first wave, and the roster could grow bigger between day one of filming and the world premiere... Please make this movie an epic one, Marvel Studios!

comment: My guess is something happens with Loki and Doctor Doom comes in and or Loki realizes Doom is a threat so he goes across different universes and brings together different teams. It fails. The universes merge and or battleworld happens. Along with that some of the older legacy characters die. And some of older MCU characters die and or some of the lesser liked characters die. I'm sure there is other actors returning they don't want to hint about. Secret Wars happens. We get legacy characters from Spider-Man, Hulk, Blade, Ghost Rider, X-Men (Wolverine and Deadpool), Original Avengers and or a version of them, along with maybe a couple others. They beat Doom. In the process the Multiverse resets. We get new actors for more than likely any character introduced pre 2017 except Spider-Man and any legacy character/actor is retired. Spider-Man 5 and or Fantastic 4 would essentially be the new start to the MCU, and then you go into the X-Men/Mutant Saga. Maybe a few stay but they will be spread out and won't be included as much. After a few more phases and or during one phase they can bring back elements of the Avengers and or Eternals. The A.X.E comic story would be interesting. They probably could end the mutant Saga with Apocalypse and or Galactus.

comment:

I’m hoping Hugh Jackman makes an appearance, so Wolverine can get a “happier” final scene with Professor X (Logan’s was heartbreaking), but I’ll understand if Hugh prefers to never pick up the claws again. The man has earned his retirement from the role, if and when he chooses it.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Please be the Doomsday that brings this franchise to an end....please be the doomsday that brings this franchise to an end...PLEASE LET THIS BE THE DOOMSDAY THAT BRINGS THIS FRANCHISE TO AN END!
Im only a few years older than this franchise existence and im tired of its presence. Its inconsistent quality, its hand in breeding disneys terrible decisions, its effect on comic book movies and how everyone keeps saying "the mcu is back!" After every other released film. And now they are so desperate to reunite attention that they're trying to convince people that Robert Downey Junior playing Doctor Doom is a good casting choice. Do you expect me to believe that they can somehow balance a probably two to three part movie with 29 people as its leads and most of the money is probably going to go to paying these actors to be in it, the giant blur of fake computer generated action scenes and a annoying ad campaign. If the point of an interconnected comic book universe is that it allows for characters to Crossover with each other then how come we don't get more just characters crossing over with each other? Even when they finally do "what if" and try for the animated medium to better tell stories? Its ugly and uncanny in replicating the actors looks and rarely has good visuals and let popularity dictate the story and turn an anthology into captain carters bizarre adventures. Moon girl and devil dinosaur is the best thing they had going for them and canceled it because another show disney owns talked about LGBT+ stuff and they wont learn that this is normal and people deservedly want to teach kids that differences in people are normal and should be respected. If you dont like someones choices, and they are not breaking a law or causing unnecessary pain or suffering to others then leave them be and get on with your day. Im certainly going to after i post this. If you want a Marvel crossover that actually has characters acting as those characters and such I heavily recommend marvels Midnight Suns video game...still pissed we will probably never get laurence fishburne back as The Beyonder.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
There’s no ground work laid out. Even with the characters no one really has an arc involving the multiverse. Hell most characters don’t even have an arc period. There’s no relationships between the characters.

Most of them will be meeting for the first time or for the first time since endgame.

Like compared to infinity war and endgame: you had arcs, deep character relationships, rivalries both friendly and not. You had characters tied to the infinity stones both literally and figuratively. You had characters tied to thanos. Either through family or through his actions. You had character arcs that spanned a decade coming to an end.

Plus you have doom from another universe as the main villain. You have multiple characters from across the multiverse included. The focus isn’t really on 616. They’re included yes but when you have characters from at least 3 different universes it doesn’t feel like the heroes will get much time to either catch up, get introduced or finish their arc.

Just seems like it’ll be a mess of a story trying to tie a bunch of stuff together and scrounge together some type of story from the multiverse saga.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Everything Matters.
It's strange that Kelsey Grammer is separate from the rest of the X-Men (Maybe he won't be Beast or maybe he will continue to be The Beast Moving forward where as all the other X-Men most likely won't continue in those roles.)
Thor at the beginning, and Mister Fantastic, and Doom at The End I get. The Captain America, Winter Soldier, Black Panther sitting next to each I get with their connection. New Falcon, Johnny Storm, Red Guardian, and M'Baku I even get with them all believing they are the Guy, but not quite The Lead. What I don't get is why Sue Storm is in the second Chair after Thor, but before Captain America. Most of the other positions that seem strange just seem to be a line break. Having her with Mister Fantastic at the end, or with Thing would have made more sense.

注：饰演反派，是漫威为影片核心反派的关键角色。
其他重要信息补充
1. 新团队与作品
雷霆特攻队（Thunderbolts）：
演员及角色：
弗洛伦斯·皮尤（叶莲娜）、大卫·哈伯（红色守护者）、怀亚特·罗素（美国密探）、汉娜·约翰-卡门（幽灵）、刘易斯·普尔曼（哨兵）等。
作品：电影《雷霆特攻队》（2025年5月2日北美上映，中国内地待定）。
特点：反英雄团队，风格类似《X特遣队》，聚焦边缘角色的“失败者联盟”。
神奇四侠（Fantastic Four）：
演员及角色：
佩德罗·帕斯卡（神奇先生）、凡妮莎·柯比（隐形女）、约瑟夫·奎因（霹雳火）、爱波·莫斯-巴克拉赫（石头人）。
作品：重启版《神奇四侠》（2024年已开拍，2025/2026年上映？需确认档期）。
概念图泄露：包含富兰克林·理查兹（神奇四侠之子）和女版银影侠（朱莉娅·加纳饰）。
2. X战警回归MCU
老版X战警演员回归：
帕特里克·斯图尔特（X教授）、伊恩·麦克莱恩（万磁王）、丽贝卡·罗梅ijn（魔形女）、詹姆斯·麦斯登（镭射眼）等均确认参与《复仇者联盟5》。
未来计划：
X战警可能衍生独立电影，与《复仇者联盟6：秘密战争》联动。
3. 重要变动与退出
伊丽莎白·奥尔森（Elizabeth Olsen）：
确认不再出演旺达·马克西莫夫（绯红女巫），退出《复仇者联盟5/6》。
原因：角色在《奇异博士2》中死亡，且演员希望回归未果。
4. 其他关键细节
导演与叙事：
罗素兄弟回归执导《复联5/6》，强调“中心叙事”以修复第四阶段分散的剧情问题。
动画角色引入：
《复联5/6》可能结合动画角色（如《假如》系列观察者、《X战警97》角色），采用真人与动画结合的形式。

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Hi, I'm back after 8 years. I last commented on "Action...Avengers: Infinity War" on behalf of all fans and myself of course. I requested certain wishes/scenarios for Avengers Infinity War & Endgame and got 4/12 unintentionally or coincidentally correct (I like to think you guys on set actually read my comment and took inspiration or had thought of those ideas already ❤️

Anways I got a few new requests for these 2 films for our Directors, Russo Brothers and of course the Man Kevin Feige.

Everybody put on there Marvel hat, it's about to get gooood (Deadpool reference)

1. Please tell us this is just half the cast for "Doomsday"

2. Have a easter egg of Avengers vs X-men somewhere in there. Like when they meet have a little brief fight between each other like our older heroes had.

3. Please have Tom Holland get his Symbiote suit. If he's not getting it in Spider Man 4.

4. Have sentimental momments with the older marvel characters and have a awesome pay offs in certain scenes.

5. If Chris Evans is coming back, either have him as Old man Steve (with the hammer or wakanda shields) or have him be Captain Hydra and then helps out last movie.

6. Have a CRAZY moment with Doom and Spider Man 📽

7. Since there's technically only 3 left of the OG Avengers (besides old Steve if he's alive🙏) Thor, Hulk and Hawkeye. Please give them a good send off if there not making after "Secret Wars". Thank You!

8. I'm gonna guess that Chris Pratt will be in "Doomsday" but can you guys please include the Guardians, Eternals, and Defenders (street level) in "Secret Wars"

9. Maybe give Captain America super soldier serum?? I don't know he was teasing around with it in "Brave New World" so.

10. You better pay off why Thor crying with Deadpool!!! (I'm 99% positive it will)

11. If some stuff gonna go down in "Doomsday" like it did in "Infinity War". Have it be some of the New Avengers and older marvel heroes come to together to fix it 😎🤘📽🙏🍿

12. Give Tobey and Hugh a pretty big moment together please 😁💯

13. Please do a big fight scene cutting to or continously going to the next character kind of shot (OMG 👀💥) (kinda like Avengers 1, Age of ultron, Endgame, and Guardians of the galaxy 3 but extremely better)

Side note Gotg3 scene was amazing BTW

14. Give us a "Avengers Assemble" again and ALSO a "To me, my X-men" moment with either Cyclops or Professor Xavier. 💯

15. Have some moments of characters teaming up there abilities 💥👀

16. Bring in Thor Force and Mavrel Zombies

17. If you do decide to have some animated scenes in one of the movies just make the whole scene animated or a little easter egg of the characters doing something on screen. Please don't take the "Space Jam" or "Roger Rabbit" route. I promise, that's on behalf of everybody. Also just make certain characters live action if you do 💯

18. Bring in our Daredevil, Punisher, Moonknight, Werewolf by Night, And all the Defenders!

19. If Punisher is in one of them... guve my boy a war machine suit. 💥🙏

20. This music you guys got playing on here. Put it in the movies either just like this playing everyone's theme when they are on screen or just keep the Avengers theme and X-men theme remixed together 😇👂👌

21. Give us a scene with Doom ripping out Thanos spine (even if it's someone else he does it to) and I a scene of Hulk holding up that big mountain like in the "Secret Wars" comics 💥👀

22. Give us Andrew Garfield back (Spider Man) and have him fight some aliens 👌😁 He's been wanting too lol

23. Somehow bring in Ty Simpkins (Harley Keener) from iron man 3 and have a Iron Man suit. (Wishful thinking)

24. Give us some crazy variants of our heroes. (Crazy I mean just be random but good and surprising, actor wise)

25. Give a scene where Doctor Strange shields everyone like in "What if?" with a protection spell 💥👀

26. Give us a scene of All The OG Marvel Heroes fighting beside each other or with the New Avengers. I personally would want a scene of just them, that would be a OG Marvel Legacy wet dream 😂 I'm sorry

27. Morgan Stark older please?

28. We want all the OG characters back. Blade, Elektra, Spider Man, Wolverine, Hulk, Fantastic Four, Punisher and Ghost Rider.
(Call them Legacy Avengers) 💥💥💥
1998-2010

29. If our OG of X-men are coming. Can you atleast bring in James McAvoy and Michael Fassbender? Even if it's a cameo scene 👌

30. Give us Infamous Iron Man!!!! 💥🤘💯

That's all I got at this time. Definitely more than the last time I was here. Thank you for reading. To everyone and Marvel Studios.

My personal thank you to everyone.

Thank You Marvel Studios
Thank You Kevin Feige
Thank You Joe and Anthony Russo
Thank You Jon Favreau
Thank You to the whole Entire Cast
Thank You to the Writers
Thank You Samuel L. Jackson
Thank You Robert Downey Jr
Thank You Chris Evans
Thank You Scarlet Johansson
Thank You Mark Ruffalo
Thank you Jeremy Renner

Thank You Ray Stevenson
Thank You William Dafoe
Thank You Alfred Molina
Thank You Thomas Haden Church
Thank You Nicolas Cage
Thank You Eric Bana
Thank Tobey Maguire
Thank You Wesley Snipes
Thank You Jack Kirby (RIP
Thank Steve Ditko (RIP
And Thank You Stan Lee (RIP), You fellas made dreams into reality and inspiration for everyone. My last wish would be that you guys would be alive to see what these amazing people are doing with your crafts.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
I find it deeply ironic that so many actors still have the opportunity to take center stage, yet RDJ—selected through a meticulously calculated marketing strategy—is, in fact, not the wrong choice. I appreciate it on some level, yet this decision inevitably fractures the carefully constructed image of Iron Man. But what else can one expect? This world thrives on profit, on ceaseless production, on the relentless churn of commerce masquerading as art.

I suspect the film will possess narrative merit, but at what cost? The so-called foundation upon which it stands—previous entries that functioned less as meaningful storytelling and more as perfunctory character introductions—renders the entire structure precarious, akin to building a house with no regard for its integrity. Can it endure the weight of monumental expectations? Or will it collapse under its own commercial excess, surviving only by virtue of the audience’s preoccupation with star power rather than substantive quality?

I doubt it will match its predecessors, which—flawed as they were—still managed to resonate. But then again, what does it matter? The machine rolls forward, indifferent to anything but its own perpetuation.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Makes me sad to see the Fox X-Men still polluting the MCU. Like does no one remember those movies were 90% AWFUL? Let them die already so you can get as far away from them as possible and do the X-Men properly for once. Between that and "jumping the Stark" with bringing RDJ back as a desperation nonsense casting for Doom - who's also a character that's had ZERO build-up leading into this so far (ohhh they mentioned Latvian heritage day in Daredevil - gimme a break)... I'm severely under-hyped for this movie.

Never doubt what the Russo's can pull off, but I give them under a 5% chance to repeat anything even close to the magnitude of Infinity War or Endgame. It's just not happening. They haven't had enough buildup time to work their magic. There won't be any "on your left", or Cap picking up Thor's hammer type of moments that resonate deeply. Any callbacks they do here will probably feel cheap and hollow by comparison. The last few years haven't been a cohesive narrative all pointing somewhere. It's just been a mish-mash of random spaghetti being thrown at the wall to see what sticks. They brought in the Russo brothers to try to right the ship in the 11th hour, but common sense tells you it's a case of "too little, too late."

Of course I'll still watch it though LOL. I'm rooting for it to succeed, if only so the door will stay open for the MCU to try getting the next 5-10 years right. And if this is the beginning of the end - which is what jumping the shark always is - ... well it was nice while it lasted. (And btw, PROFESSOR X ISN'T BLOODY BRITISH.)

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Fantastic Four (multiverse), Thunderbolts (616), X-Men (multiverse), AND a lineup for the new Avengers team, as well as a few additional characters. Bigger cast than I was expecting, but it's not bloated. That's good. If they had put EVERYONE in this, it would have been too much. And I only barely want them to increase the cast for Secret Wars, if at all.

Edit: New Avengers team is: Captain America, Thor, Black Panther, Falcon, Shang-Chi, Ant-Man, and probably Namor and Man-Ape as well (M'Baku, he's never officially taken the mantle of Man-Ape in the MCU, and it's probably better for it). Secret Wars will likely add Captain Marvel, Photon, Spider-Man, and maybe Hulk and She-Hulk to the roster. Possibly Vision, depending on what happens in his series? Though they could take a few of these and make a West Coast Avengers team alongside Wonder Man.

A Young Avengers/Champions team might be made in the future, but I don't think they'll be in Secret Wars, and they'll likely consist of Ms. Marvel, Hawkeye, Wiccan, Hulkling (do it, you cowards), White Tiger, Patriot (Eli Bradley has been seen before), and probably Speed as well.

comment:
Avengers Doomsday: Doctor Doom, Fantastic Four, Thor, Loki, Ant-Man, Shang-Chi, Thunderbolts, new Captain America, new Black Panther, the old X-Men?

Avengers Secret Wars then has a battleworld with?: Hulk, She-Hulk, Skaar, Hawkeye, Kate Bishop, Spider-Man, Captain Marvel, Ms-Marvel, Monica Rambeau, Nick Fury, G'iah, Doctor Strange, Wong, America Chavez, Vision, The Wasp, Cassie, Star-Lord, the new Guardians of the Galaxy, Sylvie, Eternals, Moon Knight, Ironheart, Wonder Man, Daredevil, Deadpool, Wolverine, the other 100 X-Men characters, and the rest of Marvel's tv shows like Punisher, Defenders, Agents of Shield, Guardians of the Multiverse & Kahhori from What If...?:

Hulk, Spider-Man, The Marvels, the smaller tv shows can all be explained. And Doctor Strange being off on his own mission. Vision is a bit lost on his own adventure. Eternals, is Eternals. Yeah..., most can be explained not to be in the Avengers movie. But Hulk should at least make it into Secret Wars imo. Spider-Man too.

But America Chavez, when will we see her again, in some Teen Avengers movie? with Cassie and so on, Kate Bishop..., is Hawkeye retired? I wouldnt mind seeing him in Secret Wars making a return, Hawkeye is part of the Avengers so..., idk?

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment: So we are finally getting all 3 teams. Finally a completed Earth. Why are we still using these Fox people? Feige continues to let his lie from the acquisition stand. Hollywood really took a look at serialized storytelling over decades and decided they were going to wed actors to these roles. Remember a decade ago when they were talking about the actors that would take in these roles in the future. They've just given up on that completely. I do not have Fox nostaligia. Those movies were not good and we need to move onto new casting if you want to reach as broad of an audience as possible. And it certainly doesn't help that they keep bringing back the ancient people to reprise roles. What is the point of having the younger Charles and Magneto if you aren't going to use them now that you have the chance. Wheeling out Patrick Stewart again is not a good look. Its giving signs of what to happened to Bruce Willis. They are literally bringing back people who started almost 3 decades ago. And they were old then. I'm kind of getting tired of this "deferment to experience" or whatever PC spin they want to put on this. Just cast new people for the X-Men already. How many more years is this going to take?

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
I legimately almost died of happiness when the X-Men cast started rolling in. I see exactly what they're going for here and what's going to be at stake for the world(s). It was the only way to do it and have stakes that made sense for each side without 30 more movies of development.

My big question: Where are the Young Avengers in all of this? Are they really not gonna show up till Secret Wars?

Mega spoilers for anyone who hasn't read the comics! You have been warned.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

So yeah we've already seen the other world that's gonna get smashed together with 616 to from Battleworld. It was in the end credits of Ms. Marvel since that version of Beast played by Kelsey Grammer, since he also mentioned Xavier being around and Beast seemed to be studying the incursions. So it's gonna be pretty much Avengers vs X-Men, and I imagine maybe some of the villains or anti-heroes might flip flop to one side or the other. I'm still curious which universe FF are from. If they are the X-Men verse, the stakes are gonna be even higher, because we expect them to make it and survive.

Also I guess they're keeping the Wanda thing under wraps still even though it's... very obvious at this point that she's coming back for the Children's Crusade/Secret Wars storyline.

title: Avengers: Doomsday | Now in Production
comment:
Is there a reason for why Robert Downey Jr. looks more like Tony Stark in this casting announcement than Victor Von Doom 🤔? And, as someone else pointed out in the comment section, this is not a complete list of actors that is going to be in Avengers: Doomsday because Tom Holland's (Mr. Spider-Man himself) chair is conspicuously absent. And, if we're to believe what the Russo Bros have been telling us the past few months now as they get ready to start shooting Doomsday next month, then Spider-Man is supposed to play a major role in both of these Avengers movies. And yet there's no chair there for Tom Holland.

Or even Benedict Cumberbatch. And Mr. Cumberbatch just revealed in an interview a couple of months back that he's going to be in both Doomsday and Secret Wars and yet there's no chair for him. And what about Hugh Jackman? I find it highly suspicious 🤨 that both Sir Ian McKellan and Sir Patrick Stewart are both in this without Hugh Jackman's Wolverine/Logan.

All three of them were very important to the success of Fox's X-Men movies. Hugh Jackman was more of a driving force behind the original X-Men movies success than James Marsden was. I mean, it'll be nice to see Cyclops again and in the MCU. But, if I had to make a choice, then I'd rather see Wolverine officially in the MCU and going up against Dr. Doom than Cyclops going up against Dr. Doom.

Hugh Jackman facing off against Robert Downey Jr. just seems like a much bigger draw to me than James Marsden going up against Robert Downey Jr. That's just my opinion 😉, though. I definitely don't think that this is the final casting call for Avengers: Doomsday. Not yet.

Not when some central characters to this story have not been announced yet (Like where is Mark Ruffalo's chair? You can't have an Avengers movie without Hulk in it.).

Slainté and Excelsior!, Marvel 🙂☕️👋
